text.tspan: Suicide rate, by age, United States, 2000 to 2019
Number of deaths from suicide per 100,000 individuals in each age group. Suicide deaths are underreported in
many countries due to social stigma and cultural or legal concerns.
Data source: WHO, Global Health Estimates (2020)
Note: To allow for comparisons between countries and over time, this metric is age-standardized.
